meta {
  name: [APISIX] deny BRP write - read-only JWT, missing write scope
  type: http
  seq: 7
}

docs {
  EXPECTED behaviour once the auth-zen APISIX plugin is implemented.

  The plugin should:
    1. Extract the subject from the Bearer JWT (scopes only contains "brp:read").
    2. Map the HTTP method (PUT) to action "write".
    3. Receive a deny decision from the policy agent because the subject lacks the "brp:write" scope.
    4. Return HTTP 403 to the client without forwarding to the upstream.

  The JWT payload used here decodes to:
    { "sub": "municipality-case-api", "organization": "urn:nl:gov:rotterdam",
      "assurance_level": "high", "roles": ["municipality_caseworker"],
      "scopes": ["brp:read"] }
}

put {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/anything
  body: json
}

headers {
  content-type: application/json
  accept: application/json
  authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJtdW5pY2lwYWxpdHktY2FzZS1hcGkiLCJvcmdhbml6YXRpb24iOiJ1cm46bmw6Z292OnJvdHRlcmRhbSIsImFzc3VyYW5jZV9sZXZlbCI6ImhpZ2giLCJyb2xlcyI6WyJtdW5pY2lwYWxpdHlfY2FzZXdvcmtlciJdLCJzY29wZXMiOlsiYnJwOnJlYWQiXX0.signature-placeholder
  x-purpose: uitvoering-wettelijke-taak
}

body:json {
  {}
}

tests {
  test("status is 403 - missing brp:write scope denied by policy agent", function() {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(403);
  });
}
